# Styling & Design System

- Styling is driven by **Tailwind v4** with an inline `@theme` block in `globals.css`.
- Treat the `@theme inline` block as the **single source of truth** for:
  - `--color-primary`, `--color-secondary`, `--color-accent`, `--color-background`, `--color-foreground`.
  - Radius scale, shadows, and font families.
- When changing brand colors:
  - Update only the relevant `--color-*` tokens in `@theme inline`.
  - Use Tailwind utilities (`bg-primary`, `text-primary`, `bg-secondary/95`, etc.) instead of hardcoded hex values in components.
- Use **section background colors** to introduce color, not inline styles:
  - Alternate between `bg-background`, `bg-primary/5`, `bg-primary/10`, or `bg-secondary/95` for major sections.
- Avoid writing arbitrary global CSS unless absolutely necessary; prefer Tailwind utilities and the existing tokens.

